1. Bybit hackers only washed away 14,300 ETH in the past 24 hours;
2. Bloomberg: Judge dismisses SEC lawsuit against Hex token founder Richard Heart;
3. Social game company ACID Labs announced the completion of $8 million in financing, led by a16z Speedrun and NFX;
4. Kaiko Research: DeFi tokens such as UNI may perform well in the second half of 2025;
5. Republican members of the U.S. Senate Banking Committee plan to review the stablecoin bill in the week of March 10;
6. The U.S. SEC postponed approval of Fidelity's spot Ethereum ETF options;
7. BlackRock plans to add 1-2% IBIT allocation to its model portfolio;
8. The name of Trump's metaverse and NFT project is rumored to be "Megaverse";
9. CME plans to launch Micro SOL futures (Micro SOL) simultaneously on March 17.
